This paper is about evaluating the accuracy of AMR parsing, which is a task related to natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new evaluation metric called SemBleu, which is based on the well-known BLEU metric for machine translation evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP and machine learning. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are also relevant to the topic of the paper.
